---
// The Project Context tab: the repo-local .hs/ Markdown files the optional
// rewrite stage reads, with the HS-47-03 guided setup and the HS-48-01
// project-doc suggestion review panel. The file list + editor content are
// populated at runtime by the knowledge behavior module; the shared kn-*
// explainer/empty styles live in SharedStyles.
---

<section id="view-hs" class="view" hidden>
  <h2>Project context</h2>
  <p class="lede">
    Context is the other part of <strong>project knowledge</strong>
    (the first is <strong>Project Facts</strong>). Where a fact is an exact
    value stamped in verbatim, context is background the rewrite model reads
    so it phrases things the way this project expects. It only takes effect
    when the optional rewrite stage is on. Edit the repo-local
    <code>.hs/</code> files here: instructions, background, workflows,
    targets, vocabulary, and ignore rules. Legacy <code>.hs_*</code> files
    are shown as read-only compatibility inputs; saving creates or updates
    the canonical <code>.hs/</code> copy.
  </p>

  {/* HS-47-02: in-app explainer — context shapes a rewrite, it is not
      substituted; static markup so the shared kn-* styles apply. */}
  <aside class="kn-explainer" aria-label="What project context is">
    <div class="kn-explainer-main">
      <p class="kn-explainer-eyebrow">Project knowledge · Context</p>
      <p class="kn-explainer-what">Background the rewrite model reads.</p>
      <p class="kn-explainer-why">
        Context is prose, not values. When the optional rewrite stage is on,
        it reads these <code>.hs/</code> notes so it phrases dictation the way
        this project expects. It shapes a rewrite; it is never copied in word
        for word. Its companion is <strong>Project Facts</strong>, which
        stamps exact values with no model.
      </p>
    </div>
    <figure class="kn-example">
      <figcaption>How context shapes a rewrite</figcaption>
      <div class="kn-example-row">
        <span class="kn-example-tag">.hs/terms.md</span>
        <code>The product is "Holdr". Use British spelling.</code>
      </div>
      <div class="kn-example-row">
        <span class="kn-example-tag">you say</span>
        <code>tell the team the color picker is done</code>
      </div>
      <div class="kn-example-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
      <div class="kn-example-row kn-example-out">
        <span class="kn-example-tag">rewrite</span>
        <code>Update the team: the Holdr colour picker is complete.</code>
      </div>
    </figure>
  </aside>

  <div id="hs-meta-banner" class="meta-banner">Loading…</div>
  {/* HS-47-02: teaching empty state when .hs/ does not exist yet. Static
      markup toggled by JS (renderHSFileList). */}
  <div id="hs-empty" class="kn-empty" hidden>
    <svg class="kn-empty-glyph" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="28" height="28" aria-hidden="true">
      <path fill="currentColor" d="M10 4H4a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v14a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h16a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V7a1 1 0 0 0-1-1h-8l-2-2Zm-5 6h14v8H5v-8Zm2 2v2h6v-2H7Z"/>
    </svg>
    <p class="kn-empty-title">No project context yet</p>
    <p class="kn-empty-text">
      Context teaches the rewrite model how this project talks: its
      vocabulary, conventions, and what to leave alone. It only takes effect
      when the optional rewrite stage is on, and nothing is written until you
      save.
    </p>
    <p class="kn-empty-eg"><code>.hs/terms.md</code> → the rewrite uses your product name and spelling</p>
    <div class="kn-empty-actions">
      <button class="btn primary" id="hs-empty-setup" type="button">Set up project knowledge</button>
      <button class="btn" id="hs-empty-example" type="button">Start with an example</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* HS-47-03: guided setup. Static markup toggled by JS. Two authoring
      paths for context (a template starter you review before it writes, or a
      copiable prompt for your own coding agent) plus a "you're set" hand-off
      to the dry-run. */}
  <section id="hs-setup" class="kn-setup panel" hidden aria-label="Set up project knowledge">
    <header class="panel-header">
      <h3>Set up project knowledge</h3>
      <button class="btn" id="hs-setup-close" type="button">Close</button>
    </header>
    <p class="kn-setup-lede">
      Two parts, both from here, no file editing. <strong>Facts</strong> are
      exact values: set them in the
      <button class="kn-linkbtn" type="button" data-section-jump="kb">Project Facts</button>
      tab. <strong>Context</strong> is guidance the rewrite model reads.
      Create it one of two ways:
    </p>
    <div class="kn-setup-grid">
      <article class="kn-setup-card">
        <h4 class="kn-setup-card-title">Use a starter set</h4>
        <p class="kn-setup-card-text">
          Create a small, well-formed <code>.hs/</code> set (instructions,
          context, terms) that you can then edit. You review exactly what will
          be written first; nothing is saved silently.
        </p>
        <button class="btn primary" id="hs-setup-starter" type="button">Create a starter set</button>
      </article>
      <article class="kn-setup-card">
        <h4 class="kn-setup-card-title">Draft with your coding agent</h4>
        <p class="kn-setup-card-text">
          Have Claude or Codex read this repo and write the <code>.hs/</code>
          files for you. Copy the prompt, paste it into your agent, then review
          the result in this tab. The drafting stays on your machine.
        </p>
        <button class="btn" id="hs-setup-copy-prompt" type="button">Copy the agent prompt</button>
        <pre class="kn-agent-prompt" id="hs-agent-prompt" aria-label="Coding-agent prompt for drafting .hs files">Loading the prompt…</pre>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div id="hs-setup-msg"></div>
  </section>
  <section class="panel hs-suggestion-panel" id="hs-suggestion-panel" hidden>
    <header class="panel-header">
      <h3>Suggested project doc update</h3>
    </header>
    <p class="rt-counter-note">
      Local intelligence can propose one narrow project-memory file after
      a dry-run. Review and edit before applying; HoldSpeak never writes
      these suggestions silently.
    </p>
    <label>
      Target path
      <input id="hs-suggestion-path" type="text" placeholder=".hs/memory/specific-slug.md" />
    </label>
    <p id="hs-suggestion-rationale" class="rt-counter-note"></p>
    <label>
      Suggested content
      <textarea id="hs-suggestion-content" placeholder="No suggestion loaded."></textarea>
    </label>
    <div id="hs-suggestion-msg"></div>
    <div class="actions">
      <button class="btn primary" id="hs-suggestion-apply" type="button">Apply to .hs</button>
      <button class="btn" id="hs-suggestion-dismiss" type="button">Dismiss</button>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="grid">
    <section class="panel">
      <header class="panel-header"><h3>Files</h3></header>
      <div id="hs-file-list" class="block-list"></div>
    </section>
    <section class="panel">
      <header class="panel-header"><h3 id="hs-editor-title">Select a .hs file</h3></header>
      <p id="hs-editor-help" class="rt-counter-note"></p>
      <textarea id="hs-editor" placeholder="Select a .hs file to edit"></textarea>
      <div id="hs-msg"></div>
      <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn primary" id="hs-btn-save" type="button">Save</button>
        <button class="btn" id="hs-btn-reset" type="button">Reset</button>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* ===== Guided setup (HS-47-03) — static markup in this template ===== */
  .kn-setup[hidden] { display: none; }
  .kn-setup-lede {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .kn-setup-lede strong { color: var(--text); }
  .kn-setup-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .kn-setup-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .kn-setup-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    padding: var(--space-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--surface-2);
  }
  .kn-setup-card-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--font-size-md);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .kn-setup-card-text {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    flex: 1;
  }
  .kn-setup-card .btn { align-self: flex-start; }
  .kn-agent-prompt {
    margin: var(--space-1) 0 0;
    max-height: 14rem;
    overflow: auto;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    background: var(--canvas);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  }
</style>
